# Canonical sources are read-only

**Never edit:**

- `DevSpecs/` in this repo (`hftr-v2.init.spec.md`)
- `agent-docs/research/v1-reference/` — the vendored v1 snapshot in this repo
- The external v1 workspace (`/Users/matt-mobile/MATT/web_dev/hftr/`) — history only

## Independence rule (D-015)

v2 must never depend on the external v1 workspace at build, seed, or runtime. Everything v2
consumes from v1 is vendored in-repo: reference snapshot at `agent-docs/research/v1-reference/`
(read-only) and seed catalogs at `packages/db/src/seed/catalogs/` (canonical for v2; edit with
`catalog_version` bumps). If new v1 material is needed, vendor it in and record provenance in
`agent-docs/research/v1-carryover.md`.

## Build alignment rule

All v2 work must align with **combined intent** from:

1. v2 init spec (`DevSpecs/hftr-v2.init.spec.md`)
2. v1 project (specs, agent-docs, contracts, wiki, pipeline research)

When they conflict, record resolution in `agent-docs/dev-intent/decisions-log.md` (stable D-nnn ID).
Do not silently pick one source.

## What to carry from v1

- **Contracts and catalogs** — types, bands, guardrails, verification schemas
- **Invariants and compliance framing**
- **Research and wiki concepts**

Do **not** copy v1 components, stale DB types, or stub LLM/broker layers blindly.
Mapping lives in `agent-docs/research/v1-carryover.md`.

## Instead of editing canonical files

- Record implementation truth in `agent-docs/`
- Port contracts into `packages/contracts/` with v2 naming
- Log open questions as OQ-n in decisions-log (resolve, never delete)
